--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 85d6d3d56ef0e2449a6eb0497f72471f, type: 3}
  m_Name: t2_diabetes
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: AnatomiQ.Data::AnatomiQ.Data.DiseaseAsset
  SchemaVersion: 1
  DiseaseId: t2_diabetes
  DisplayName: Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus
  ShortLabel: Type 2 Diabetes
  Category: 0
  Icd10Code: E11
  Description: A chronic metabolic disorder characterized by insulin resistance and
    progressive pancreatic beta cell dysfunction, leading to sustained hyperglycemia
    and progressive multi-organ complications affecting the cardiovascular, renal,
    ocular, and nervous systems.
  EntryOrganId: pancreas_beta_cells
  Stages:
  - StageId: early
    Label: "Early (0\u20135 years)"
    Description: Insulin resistance develops; pancreas compensates with hyperinsulinemia;
      blood glucose begins to rise.
    StepIndices: 00000000010000000200000003000000
  - StageId: intermediate
    Label: "Intermediate (5\u201315 years)"
    Description: Beta cell function declines; sustained hyperglycemia damages microvasculature;
      early end-organ changes.
    StepIndices: 04000000050000000600000007000000
  - StageId: advanced
    Label: Advanced (15+ years)
    Description: Established microvascular and macrovascular complications across
      multiple organ systems.
    StepIndices: 08000000090000000a000000
  Cascade:
  - StepIndex: 0
    Stage: early
    TargetOrganId: pancreas_beta_cells
    MechanismKey: beta_cell_hyperinsulinemia
    Severity: 25
    DelayMs: 0
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 0
      Color: '#FFB800'
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0.5
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Pancreatic beta cells become hypersensitive to glucose and
      begin secreting excess insulin to compensate for rising tissue insulin resistance.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: compensatory hyperinsulinemia
      ClinicalNote: Asymptomatic phase, often missed without targeted screening.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 1
    Stage: early
    TargetOrganId: tissues_peripheral
    MechanismKey: insulin_resistance
    Severity: 35
    DelayMs: 2500
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 1
      Color: 
      FromColor: '#E8B5A8'
      ToColor: '#D49888'
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 2500
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Muscle and fat tissues progressively lose sensitivity to insulin,
      requiring ever-higher insulin levels to maintain normal glucose uptake.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: peripheral insulin resistance
      ClinicalNote: Linked to obesity, sedentary lifestyle, and genetic predisposition.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 2
    Stage: early
    TargetOrganId: blood_glucose_serum
    MechanismKey: hyperglycemia_onset
    Severity: 45
    DelayMs: 5000
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 1
      Color: 
      FromColor: '#C44545'
      ToColor: '#E8A040'
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 2500
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Despite elevated insulin, blood glucose rises above the normal
      range as compensation begins to fail. This marks the clinical onset of diabetes.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: sustained hyperglycemia
      ClinicalNote: HbA1c crosses 6.5% threshold for diagnosis.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 3
    Stage: early
    TargetOrganId: kidney_glomerulus
    MechanismKey: glomerular_hyperfiltration
    Severity: 30
    DelayMs: 8000
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 0
      Color: '#FFA040'
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0.5
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: The kidneys initially respond to high blood glucose by increasing
      filtration rate, a phase known as glomerular hyperfiltration.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: early diabetic nephropathy hyperfiltration phase
      ClinicalNote: Reversible if glycemic control achieved.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 4
    Stage: intermediate
    TargetOrganId: pancreas_beta_cells
    MechanismKey: beta_cell_exhaustion
    Severity: 65
    DelayMs: 11500
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 4
      Color: 
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0.88
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 2500
    NarrationFallback: Years of overwork drive beta cell exhaustion. Insulin output
      progressively declines, accelerating the rise in blood glucose.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: beta cell apoptosis and dysfunction
      ClinicalNote: Many patients now require oral medications or insulin.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 5
    Stage: intermediate
    TargetOrganId: blood_vessels_systemic
    MechanismKey: microvascular_basement_thickening
    Severity: 55
    DelayMs: 14500
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 5
      Color: 
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 1.3
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 3000
    NarrationFallback: Sustained high glucose causes thickening of small blood vessel
      walls throughout the body, reducing oxygen delivery to tissues.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: advanced glycation end products and microvascular damage
      ClinicalNote: The mechanism behind the major complications that follow.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 6
    Stage: intermediate
    TargetOrganId: eye_retina
    MechanismKey: diabetic_retinopathy_early
    Severity: 50
    DelayMs: 17500
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 0
      Color: '#D44545'
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0.7
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Damaged retinal capillaries begin to leak and form microaneurysms,
      the earliest visible sign of diabetic eye disease.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: non-proliferative diabetic retinopathy
      ClinicalNote: Often asymptomatic until significant; annual eye exams critical.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 7
    Stage: intermediate
    TargetOrganId: nerves_peripheral_lower
    MechanismKey: diabetic_neuropathy_early
    Severity: 45
    DelayMs: 20500
    DurationMs: 3000
    Effect:
      Type: 1
      Color: 
      FromColor: '#FFE8C8'
      ToColor: '#D49888'
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 2500
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Peripheral nerves, especially in the feet and legs, lose function
      due to vascular damage. Patients may notice tingling or reduced sensation.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: distal symmetric polyneuropathy
      ClinicalNote: Increases risk of unnoticed foot injuries and ulcers.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 8
    Stage: advanced
    TargetOrganId: kidney_left
    MechanismKey: chronic_kidney_disease
    Severity: 80
    DelayMs: 23500
    DurationMs: 3500
    Effect:
      Type: 1
      Color: 
      FromColor: '#A85C45'
      ToColor: '#6B3825'
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 3000
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Years of glomerular damage progress to chronic kidney disease.
      Kidney function declines, protein leaks into the urine, and waste products
      accumulate.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: diabetic nephropathy with declining GFR
      ClinicalNote: Diabetes is the leading cause of end-stage renal disease worldwide.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 9
    Stage: advanced
    TargetOrganId: blood_vessels_coronary
    MechanismKey: accelerated_atherosclerosis
    Severity: 85
    DelayMs: 27000
    DurationMs: 3500
    Effect:
      Type: 5
      Color: 
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: 
      Rate: 0
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 1.6
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 3500
    NarrationFallback: Diabetes accelerates atherosclerosis throughout the body.
      Coronary arteries narrow, dramatically increasing the risk of heart attack.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: diabetic macrovascular disease
      ClinicalNote: Cardiovascular disease causes the majority of deaths in T2DM.
      Audience: 0
  - StepIndex: 10
    Stage: advanced
    TargetOrganId: eye_retina
    MechanismKey: proliferative_retinopathy
    Severity: 90
    DelayMs: 30500
    DurationMs: 3500
    Effect:
      Type: 2
      Color: 
      FromColor: 
      ToColor: 
      Intensity: 0
      FadeMs: 0
      ParticleType: inflammation
      Rate: 40
      Scale: 0
      ThicknessFactor: 0
      FromOrganId: 
      ToOrganId: 
      DurationMs: 0
    NarrationFallback: Without intervention, fragile new blood vessels grow on the
      retina and rupture. This is proliferative retinopathy and a leading cause of
      preventable blindness.
    AiContext:
      Physiology: proliferative diabetic retinopathy
      ClinicalNote: Treatable with laser photocoagulation if caught early.
      Audience: 0
  Metadata:
    Sources:
    - "StatPearls \u2014 Type 2 Diabetes (NCBI Bookshelf, 2023)"
    - Swedish National Diabetes Register cohort study (Lancet Diabetes Endocrinol)
    - ADA Standards of Care 2024
    MedicalReviewedBy: 
    MedicalReviewedDate: 
    Version: 0.9-pre-review
    TotalDurationMs: 34000
    StepCount: 11
